Iran und zeigt, wie Kants Denken einen festen Platz im philosophischen Diskurs des Iran erhalten hat.  aIn Iran, Kant is one of the most widely read Western philosophers. His works have been acknowledged by a broad variety of philosophical and political camps and discussed in relationship to Islamic philosophers such as Ibn Sina (Avicenna) and Mulla Sadra. This study examines the contexts and approaches to Kant’s reception in Iran and shows how Kant’s thought has maintained a solid place in Iranian philosophical discourse.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aPhilosophyzIranxHistory. 4aIran. 4aIslamische Philosophie. 4aKantforschung. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aIran.  aKant research Islamic philosophy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2015 Part 1z978311076251808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2014z9783110370393oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831103912130 cprintz978311036375340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311036482840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110364828423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110364828/original  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-11-076251-8  DG Plus DeG Package 2015 Part 1b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-DPHb2014